# Observable weights for LEP hadronization tuning (e+e- at 91.2 GeV)
# Format: /regex/path/to/histogram   weight
# Paths are matched as regex against the YODA analysis path.
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Parameters under study: StringZ:aLund, StringZ:bLund, StringPT:sigma
# Primary observable sensitivity:
#   aLund, bLund -> thrust, heavy-jet mass, C-parameter, jet rates
#   sigma        -> transverse momentum distributions, jet broadening
# ALEPH QCD study -- event shapes and jet rates at 91.2 GeV (broadest coverage)
/ALEPH_1996_I428072   1.0
# OPAL event shape distributions and moments (91-209 GeV, largest data set)
/OPAL_2004_I669402    1.0
# DELPHI MC tuning reference -- event shapes and identified particles
/DELPHI_1996_I424112  1.0
# ALEPH charged multiplicity -- overall hadron yield constraint
/ALEPH_1991_I319520   2.0
